{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603423","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603423"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:37:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:37:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15751"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15751"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8442"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62452"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8442","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8442"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15751"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47899"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"8579"},{"type":"tags","id":"10631"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20316"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20319"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62452","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62452"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIn vitro fertilisation (IVF) is a complex assisted reproductive technology involving multiple steps.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a key step in the in vitro fertilisation process?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Transvaginal oocyte collection","Ovarian hyperstimulation suppression","Natural cycle monitoring only","Direct fallopian tube insemination","Spontaneous ovulation timing"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe IVF process involves several key steps:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransvaginal oocyte collection\u003C/strong\u003E is performed under ultrasound guidance following controlled ovarian stimulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOvarian hyperstimulation suppression\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - controlled ovarian hyperstimulation is actually required to produce multiple follicles\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENatural cycle monitoring\u003C/strong\u003E alone is insufficient for IVF success\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect fallopian tube insemination\u003C/strong\u003E describes intrauterine insemination, not IVF\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpontaneous ovulation timing\u003C/strong\u003E is not used in IVF as precise timing control is needed\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter oocyte collection, the eggs are fertilised with prepared sperm in the laboratory. Resulting embryos are cultured before transfer to the uterus.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["In vitro fertilisation requires oocyte collection via transvaginal ultrasound-guided aspiration following controlled ovarian hyperstimulation.","Controlled ovarian hyperstimulation uses gonadotropins to stimulate multiple follicle development.","IVF involves oocyte collection, sperm preparation, fertilisation in culture, and embryo transfer."],"references":["Wang J, Sauer MV. In vitro fertilization (IVF): a review of 3 decades of clinical innovation and technological advancement. Ther Clin Risk Manag. 2006 Dec;2(4):355-64. doi: 10.2147/tcrm.2006.2.4.355. PMID: 18360648; PMCID: PMC1936357.","Choe J, Shanks AL. In Vitro Fertilization. [Updated 2023 Sep 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK562266/","Eskew AM, Jungheim ES. A History of Developments to Improve in vitro Fertilization. Mo Med. 2017 May-Jun;114(3):156-159. PMID: 30228571; PMCID: PMC6140213.","Singh K, Dewani D. Recent Advancements in In Vitro Fertilisation. Cureus. 2022 Oct 10;14(10):e30116. doi: 10.7759/cureus.30116. PMID: 36381837; PMCID: PMC9644046."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47899"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15751"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47899"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-17T20:29:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-17T20:30:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8442"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62452"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4935","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4935"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd5a","name":"